7. The Single Rule That Keeps a Game Alive

A game token survives when:

Demand for the token > reward emission

or equivalently:

Spend + Burn ≥ Rewards

If this inequality fails, the token price eventually approaches zero.

Strategic Conclusion

The dominant mistake of P2E systems:

They optimized for player rewards,
not for economic balance.

Your architecture—AI spending, burn mechanics, and resource extraction—moves in the correct direction, but it will only work if token spending inside the world remains higher than token emission.

